text: Olena Zhupina (, born 23 August 1973 in Zaporizhzhia) is a female diver from Ukraine. ==Career== She who won the bronze medal with Ganna Sorokina in the Women's 3m Synchronized Springboard competition at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Australia. Zhupina also competed in the 1996 Summer Olympics and the 2004 Summer Olympics.Sports-Reference She has 28 medals total, 13 of which are gold. In April 2002, she took the first place in Stockholm, Sweden, in the European Champions Cup in synchronous springboard diving. In 2001, she participated at the 4th SuperFinal of the Grand Prix which was held in Athens, Greece.Motor Sich ==References== Category:1973 births Category:Ukrainian female divers Category:Living people Category:Divers at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Divers at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:Divers at the 2004 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic divers of Ukraine Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Ukraine Category:People from Zaporizhia Category:Olympic medalists in diving Category:Medalists at the 2000 Summer Olympics Category:World Aquatics Championships medalists Category:Universiade medalists in diving Category:Universiade silver medalists for Ukraine Category:Medalists at the 2001 Summer Universiade
